    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-06T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="786"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/239: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-07T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 7, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 7—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Embassy’s 246, December 19, 3 p.m.<note n="64" xml:id="d786fn64">
                        <ref target="frus1935v03#pg_937">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 937</ref>.</note> I discussed the
                    situation of the oil companies today with the Vice Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs<note n="65" xml:id="d786fn65">Mamoru Shigemitsu.</note> on the basis
                    of paragraph 4 of Embassy’s 240 December 13, 6 p.m.<note n="66"
                        xml:id="d786fn66">
                        <ref target="frus1935v03#pg_935">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1935, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 935</ref>.</note> The Vice Minister
                    made no comment except to say that the Government had no intention to deprive
                    the foreign companies of a reasonable economic return and that he would see what
                    if anything could be done.</p>
                <p>The Dutch Minister recently made similar representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
